Module AM25_myShelfie
Package it.polimi.ingsw.model

Class Player

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.model.Player
public class Player extends Object
Player is a class that models the player in a game. This class contains all the information regarding a player of the game. Its active role in the mode is being an hub for the management of the operation regarding the player itself

  • Constructor Details

    • Player

      public Player(String name, LivingRoom board, PersonalGoal personalGoal)
      The constructor of Player requires all his attributes to be passed as parameters except for the shelf that is initialized outside the contructor
      Parameters:
      name - is the unique nickname of the player in the game
      board - is the reference to the living room used in the game
      personalGoal - is the personal goal that the player have to accomplish. Note that personalGoal being a parameter of the constructor is important because initializing it inside player would have made difficult making sure that players in the same game does not share the same personalGoal

    • moveTiles

      public void moveTiles(List<Tile> tiles, int shelfColumn) throws NotInLineException, NoFreeEdgeException, OutOfBoundException, NullPointerException, FullColumnException, InvalidTileException
      moveTiles is the core method of player used to take a list of Tile from the living room and placing them into the shelf Player have to check that adding tiles to the shelf will be legal in order to avoid taking the tiles if the move throws an exception
      Parameters:
      tiles - is the list of tiles that the player want to take from the board. The order of the list mirrors the order in which the player wants to place them into the shelf
      shelfColumn - is the index of the column of the shelf in which the player wants to place the tiles
      Throws:
      NotInLineException - if the tiles are not in a straight line
      NoFreeEdgeException - if one tile has no free adjacent cells
      OutOfBoundException - if one coordinate is out of the board
      NullPointerException - if one cell is empty
      FullColumnException - if the tiles couldn't fit in the selected column
      InvalidTileException

    • isBookshelfFull

      public boolean isBookshelfFull()
